items.name: Bulbasaur
items.description: The Seed Pokémon. It can go for days without eating a single morsel. In the bulb on its back, it stores energy.

items.name: Ivysaur
items.description: The Seed Pokémon. The bud on its back grows by drawing energy. It gives off an aroma when it is ready to bloom.

items.name: Venusaur
items.description: The Seed Pokémon. The flower on its back catches the sun’s rays. The sunlight is then absorbed and used for energy

items.name: Charmander
items.description: The Lizard Pokémon. The flame at the tip of its tail makes a sound as it burns. You can only hear it in quiet places.

items.name: Charmeleon
items.description: The Flame Pokémon. Tough fights could excite this Pokémon. When excited, it may breathe out bluish-white flames.

items.name: Charizard
items.description: The Flame Pokémon. When this Pokémon expels a blast of superhot fire, the red flame at the tip of its tail burns more intensely.

items.name: Squirtle
items.description: The Tiny Turtle Pokémon. Shoots water at prey while in the water. Withdraws into its shell when in danger.

items.name: Wartortle
items.description: The Turtle Pokémon. When tapped on its head, this Pokémon will pull it in, but its tail will still stick out a little bit.

items.name: Blastoise
items.description: The Shellfish Pokémon. Once it takes aim at its enemy, it blasts out water with even more force than a fire hose.

items.name: Caterpie
items.description: The Worm Pokémon. If you touch the feeler on top of its head, it will release a horrible stink to protect itself.

items.name: Metapod
items.description: The Cocoon Pokémon. Hardens its shell to protect itself. However, a large impact may cause it to pop out of its shell.

items.name: Butterfree
items.description: The Butterfly Pokémon. Its wings, covered with poisonous powder, repel water. This allows it to fly in the rain.

items.name: Weedle
items.description: The Hairy Bug Pokémon. Beware of the sharp stinger on its head. It hides in grass and bushes where it eats leaves.

items.name: Kakuna
items.description: The Cocoon Pokémon. Able to move only slightly. When endangered, it may stick out its stinger and poison its enemy.

items.name: Beedrill
items.description: The Poison Bee Pokémon. It has three poisonous stingers on its forelegs and its tail. They are used to jab its enemy repeatedly.

items.name: Pidgey
items.description: The Tiny Bird Pokémon. Very docile. If attacked, it will often kick up sand to protect itself rather than fight back.

items.name: Pidgeotto
items.description: The Bird Pokémon. This Pokémon is full of vitality. It constantly flies around its large territory in search of prey.

items.name: Pidgeot
items.description: The Bird Pokémon. This Pokémon flies at Mach 2 speed, seeking prey. Its large talons are feared as wicked weapons.

items.name: Rattata
items.description: The Mouse Pokémon. Will chew on anything with its fangs. If you see one, you can be certain that 40 more live in the area.

items.name: Raticate
items.description: The Mouse Pokémon. Its hind feet are webbed. They act as flippers, so it can swim in rivers and hunt for prey.

items.name: Spearow
items.description: The Tiny Bird Pokémon. Inept at flying high. However, it can fly around very fast to protect its territory.

items.name: Fearow
items.description: The Beak Pokémon. A Pokémon that dates back many years. If it senses danger, it flies high and away, instantly.

items.name: Ekans
items.description: The Snake Pokémon. The older it gets, the longer it grows. At night, it wraps its long body around tree branches to rest.

items.name: Arbok
items.description: The Cobra Pokémon. The frightening patterns on its belly have been studied. Six variations have been confirmed.

items.name: Pikachu
items.description: The Mouse Pokémon. This forest-dwelling Pokémon stores electricity in its cheeks, so you’ll feel a tingly shock if you touch it.

items.name: Raichu
items.description: The Mouse Pokémon. When electricity builds up inside its body, it becomes feisty. It also glows in the dark.

items.name: Sandshrew
items.description: The Mouse Pokémon. Its body is dry. When it gets cold at night, its hide is said to become coated with a fine dew.

items.name: Sandslash
items.description: The Mouse Pokémon. It is skilled at slashing enemies with its claws. If broken, they start to grow back in a day.

items.name: Nidoran ♀
items.description: The Poison Pin Pokémon. A mild-mannered Pokémon that does not like to fight. Beware—its small horn secretes venom.

items.name: Nidorina
items.description: The Poison Pin Pokémon. When resting deep in its burrow, its barbs always retract. This is proof that it is relaxed.

items.name: Nidoqueen
items.description: The Drill Pokémon. Tough scales cover the sturdy body of this Pokémon. It appears that the scales grow in cycles.

items.name: Nidoran ♂
items.description: The Poison Pin Pokémon. Its large ears are always kept upright. If it senses danger, it will attack with a poisonous sting.

items.name: Nidorino
items.description: The Poison Pin Pokémon. Its horn contains venom. If it stabs an enemy with the horn, the impact makes the poison leak out.

items.name: Nidoking
items.description: The Drill Pokémon. Its steel-like hide adds to its powerful tackle. Its horns are so hard, they can pierce a diamond.

items.name: Clefairy
items.description: The Fairy Pokémon. Adored for their cute looks and playfulness. They are thought to be rare, as they do not appear often.

items.name: Clefable
items.description: The Fairy Pokémon. They appear to be very protective of their own world. It is a kind of fairy, rarely seen by people.

items.name: Vulpix
items.description: The Fox Pokémon. Both its fur and its tails are beautiful. As it grows, the tails split and form more tails.

items.name: Ninetales
items.description: The Fox Pokémon. According to an enduring legend, nine noble saints were united and reincarnated as this Pokémon.

items.name: Jigglypuff
items.description: The Balloon Pokémon. Uses its cute round eyes to enrapture its foe. It then sings a pleasing melody that lulls the foe to sleep.

items.name: Wigglytuff
items.description: The Balloon Pokémon. Its body is very elastic. By inhaling deeply, it can continue to inflate itself without limit.

items.name: Zubat
items.description: The Bat Pokémon. Emits ultrasonic cries while it flies. They act as a sonar used to check for objects in its way.

items.name: Golbat
items.description: The Bat Pokémon. It attacks in a stealthy manner, without warning. Its sharp fangs are used to bite and to suck blood.

items.name: Oddish
items.description: The Weed Pokémon. It may be mistaken for a clump of weeds. If you try to yank it out of the ground, it shrieks horribly.

items.name: Gloom
items.description: The Weed Pokémon. Smells incredibly foul! However, around one out of a thousand people enjoy sniffing its nose-bending stink.

items.name: Vileplume
items.description: The Flower Pokémon. Flaps its broad flower petals to scatter its poisonous pollen. The flapping sound is very loud.

items.name: Paras
items.description: The Mushroom Pokémon. Burrows under the ground to gnaw on tree roots. The mushrooms on its back absorb most of the nutrition.

items.name: Parasect
items.description: The Mushroom Pokémon. The bug host is drained of energy by the mushroom on its back. The mushroom appears to do all the thinking.

items.name: Venonat
items.description: The Insect Pokémon. Its large eyes act as radar. In a bright place, you can see that they are clusters of many tiny eyes.

items.name: Venomoth
items.description: The Poison Moth Pokémon. The powdery scales on its wings are hard to remove from skin. They also contain poison that leaks out on contact.

items.name: Diglett
items.description: The Mole Pokémon. It prefers dark places. It spends most of its time underground, though it may pop up in caves.

items.name: Dugtrio
items.description: The Mole Pokémon. A team of triplets that can burrow to a depth of 60 miles. It’s reported that this triggers an earthquake.

items.name: Meowth
items.description: The Scratch Cat Pokémon. Appears to be more active at night. It loves round and shiny things. It can’t stop itself from picking them up.

items.name: Persian
items.description: The Classy Cat Pokémon. The gem in its forehead glows on its own! It walks with all the grace and elegance of a proud queen.

items.name: Psyduck
items.description: The Duck Pokémon. Always tormented by headaches. It uses psychic powers, but whether it intends to do so is not known.

items.name: Golduck
items.description: The Duck Pokémon. Its long, slim limbs end in broad flippers. They are used for swimming gracefully in lakes.

items.name: Mankey
items.description: The Pig Monkey Pokémon. An agile Pokémon that lives in trees. It angers easily and will not hesitate to attack anything.

items.name: Primeape
items.description: The Pig Monkey Pokémon. It stops being angry only when nobody else is around. To view this moment is very difficult.

items.name: Growlithe
items.description: The Puppy Pokémon. A Pokémon with a friendly nature. However, it will bark fiercely at anything invading its territory.

items.name: Arcanine
items.description: The Legendary Pokémon. A legendary Pokémon in the East. Many people are charmed by the grace and beauty of its running.

items.name: Poliwag
items.description: The Tadpole Pokémon. The direction of the spiral on the belly differs by area. It is more adept at swimming than walking.

items.name: Poliwhirl
items.description: The Tadpole Pokémon. Under attack, it uses its belly spiral to put the foe to sleep. It then makes its escape.

items.name: Poliwrath
items.description: The Tadpole Pokémon. Swims powerfully using all the muscles in its body. It can even overtake world-class swimmers.

items.name: Abra
items.description: The Psi Pokémon. Sleeps 18 hours a day. If it senses danger, it will teleport itself to safety even as it sleeps.

items.name: Kadabra
items.description: The Psi Pokémon. Many odd things happen if this Pokémon is close by. For example, it makes clocks run backward.

items.name: Alakazam
items.description: The Psi Pokémon. A Pokémon that can memorize anything. It never forgets what it learns—that’s why this Pokémon is smart.

items.name: Machop
items.description: The Superpower Pokémon. Very powerful in spite of its small size. Its mastery of many types of martial arts makes it very tough.

items.name: Machoke
items.description: The Superpower Pokémon. The belt around its waist holds back its energy. Without it, this Pokémon would be unstoppable.

items.name: Machamp
items.description: The Superpower Pokémon. One arm alone can move mountains. Using all four arms, this Pokémon fires off awesome punches.

items.name: Bellsprout
items.description: The Flower Pokémon. Prefers hot and humid places. It ensnares tiny bugs with its vines and devours them.

items.name: Weepinbell
items.description: The Flycatcher Pokémon. When hungry, it swallows anything that moves. Its hapless prey is dissolved by strong acids.

items.name: Victreebel
items.description: The Flycatcher Pokémon. Lures prey with the sweet aroma of honey. Swallowed whole, the prey is dissolved in a day, bones and all.

items.name: Tentacool
items.description: The Jellyfish Pokémon. It can sometimes be found all dry and shriveled up on a beach. Toss it back into the sea to revive it.

items.name: Tentacruel
items.description: The Jellyfish Pokémon. Its 80 tentacles can stretch and contract freely. They wrap around prey and weaken it with poison.

items.name: Geodude
items.description: The Rock Pokémon. Commonly found near mountain trails and the like. If you step on one by accident, it gets angry.

items.name: Graveler
items.description: The Rock Pokémon. Often seen rolling down mountain trails. Obstacles are just things to roll straight over, not avoid.

items.name: Golem
items.description: The Megaton Pokémon. Once it sheds its skin, its body turns tender and whitish. Its hide hardens when it’s exposed to air.

items.name: Ponyta
items.description: The Fire Horse Pokémon. Capable of jumping incredibly high. Its hooves and sturdy legs absorb the impact of a hard landing.

items.name: Rapidash
items.description: The Fire Horse Pokémon. Just loves to run. If it sees something faster than itself, it will give chase at top speed.

items.name: Slowpoke
items.description: The Dopey Pokémon. Incredibly slow and sluggish. It is quite content to loll about without worrying about the time.

items.name: Slowbro
items.description: The Hermit Crab Pokémon. Lives lazily by the sea. If the Shellder on its tail comes off, it becomes a Slowpoke again.

items.name: Magnemite
items.description: The Magnet Pokémon. It is hatched with the ability to defy gravity. It floats while emitting powerful electromagnetic waves.

items.name: Magneton
items.description: The Magnet Pokémon. Generates strange radio signals. It raises the temperature by 3.6 degrees Fahrenheit within 3,300 feet.

items.name: Farfetch'd
items.description: The Wild Duck Pokémon. They live where reedy plants grow. Farfetch’d are rarely seen, so it’s thought their numbers are decreasing.

items.name: Doduo
items.description: The Twin Bird Pokémon. Its short wings make flying difficult. Instead, this Pokémon runs at high speed on developed legs.

items.name: Dodrio
items.description: The Triple Bird Pokémon. One of Doduo’s two heads splits to form a unique species. It runs close to 40 mph in prairies.

items.name: Seel
items.description: The Sea Lion Pokémon. Loves freezing-cold conditions. Relishes swimming in a frigid climate of around 14 degrees Fahrenheit.

items.name: Dewgong
items.description: The Sea Lion Pokémon. Its entire body is a snowy white. Unharmed by even intense cold, it swims powerfully in icy waters.

items.name: Grimer
items.description: The Sludge Pokémon. Made of congealed sludge. It smells too putrid to touch. Even weeds won’t grow in its path.

items.name: Muk
items.description: The Sludge Pokémon. Smells so awful, it can cause fainting. Through degeneration of its nose, it lost its sense of smell.

items.name: Shellder
items.description: The Bivalve Pokémon. The shell can withstand any attack. However, when it is open, the tender body is exposed.

items.name: Cloyster
items.description: The Bivalve Pokémon. For protection, it uses its harder-than-diamond shell. It also shoots spikes from the shell.

items.name: Gastly
items.description: The Gas Pokémon. Said to appear in decrepit, deserted buildings. It has no real shape, as it appears to be made of a gas.

items.name: Haunter
items.description: The Gas Pokémon. By licking, it saps the victim’s life. It causes shaking that won’t stop until the victim’s demise.

items.name: Gengar
items.description: The Shadow Pokémon. A Gengar is close by if you feel a sudden chill. It may be trying to lay a curse on you.

items.name: Onix
items.description: The Rock Snake Pokémon. Burrows at high speed in search of food. The tunnels it leaves are used as homes by Diglett.

items.name: Drowzee
items.description: The Hypnosis Pokémon. If you sleep by it all the time, it will sometimes show you dreams it had eaten in the past.

items.name: Hypno
items.description: The Hypnosis Pokémon. Avoid eye contact if you come across one. It will try to put you to sleep by using its pendulum.

items.name: Krabby
items.description: The River Crab Pokémon. Its pincers are superb weapons. They sometimes break off during battle, but they grow back fast.

items.name: Kingler
items.description: The Pincer Pokémon. One claw grew massively and is as hard as steel. It has 10,000-horsepower strength. However, it is too heavy.

items.name: Voltorb
items.description: The Ball Pokémon. It is said to camouflage itself as a Poké Ball. It will self-destruct with very little stimulus.

items.name: Electrode
items.description: The Ball Pokémon. Stores electrical energy inside its body. Even the slightest shock could trigger a huge explosion.

items.name: Exeggcute
items.description: The Egg Pokémon. The heads attract each other and spin around. There must be six heads for it to maintain balance.

items.name: Exeggutor
items.description: The Coconut Pokémon. Its cries are very noisy. This is because each of the three heads thinks about whatever it likes.

items.name: Cubone
items.description: The Lonely Pokémon. Wears the skull of its deceased mother. Its cries echo inside the skull and come out as a sad melody.

items.name: Marowak
items.description: The Bone Keeper Pokémon. Small and weak, this Pokémon is adept with its bone club. It has grown more vicious over the ages.

items.name: Hitmonlee
items.description: The Kicking Pokémon. When kicking, the sole of its foot turns as hard as a diamond on impact and destroys its enemy.

items.name: Hitmonchan
items.description: The Punching Pokémon. Punches in corkscrew fashion. It can punch its way through a concrete wall like a drill.

items.name: Lickitung
items.description: The Licking Pokémon. Its tongue spans almost seven feet and moves more freely than its forelegs. Its licks can cause paralysis.

items.name: Koffing

conditions.value: while in a region with significant anthropogenic pollution

items.description: The Poison Gas Pokémon. In hot places, its internal gases could expand and explode without any warning. Be very careful!

items.name: Weezing
items.description: The Poison Gas Pokémon. This Pokémon lives and grows by absorbing poison gas, dust, and germs that exist inside garbage.

items.name: Rhyhorn
items.description: The Spikes Pokémon. A Pokémon with a one-track mind. Once it charges, it won’t stop running until it falls asleep.

items.name: Rhydon
items.description: The Drill Pokémon. Its brain developed when it began walking on its hind legs. Its armor-like hide even repels molten lava.

items.name: Chansey
items.description: The Egg Pokémon. A gentle and kindhearted Pokémon that shares its nutritious eggs if it sees an injured Pokémon.

items.name: Tangela
items.description: The Vine Pokémon. Its identity is obscured by masses of thick blue vines. The vines are said to never stop growing.

items.name: Kangaskhan
items.description: The Parent Pokémon. Raises its young in its belly pouch. Won’t run from any fight to keep its young protected.

items.name: Horsea
items.description: The Dragon Pokémon. If it senses any danger, it will vigorously spray water or a special type of ink from its mouth.

items.name: Seadra
items.description: The Dragon Pokémon. Touching the back fin causes numbness. It hooks its tail to coral to stay in place while sleeping.

items.name: Goldeen
items.description: The Goldfish Pokémon. When it is time for them to lay eggs, they can be seen swimming up rivers and falls in large groups.

items.name: Seaking
items.description: The Goldfish Pokémon. It is the male’s job to make a nest by carving out boulders in a stream using the horn on its head.

items.name: Staryu
items.description: The Star Shape Pokémon. As long as the center section is unharmed, this Pokémon can grow back fully even if it is chopped to bits.

items.name: Starmie
items.description: The Mysterious Pokémon. The center section is named the core. People think it is communicating when it glows in seven colors.

items.name: Mr. Mime
items.description: The Barrier Pokémon. Always practicing its pantomime act. It makes enemies believe something exists that really doesn’t.

items.name: Scyther
items.description: The Mantis Pokémon. Leaps out of tall grass and slices prey with its scythes. The movement looks like that of a ninja.

items.name: Jynx
items.description: The Human Shape Pokémon. Appears to move to a rhythm of its own, as if it were dancing. It wiggles its hips as it walks.

items.name: Electabuzz
items.description: The Electric Pokémon. If a major power outage occurs, it is certain that this Pokémon has eaten electricity at a power plant.

items.name: Magmar
items.description: The Spitfire Pokémon. Born in an active volcano. Its body is always cloaked in flames, so it looks like a big ball of fire.

items.name: Pinsir
items.description: The Stag Beetle Pokémon. Grips its prey in its pincers and squeezes hard! It can’t move if it’s cold out, so it lives in warm places.

items.name: Tauros
items.description: The Wild Bull Pokémon. A rowdy Pokémon with a lot of stamina. Once running, it won’t stop until it hits something.

items.name: Magikarp
items.description: The Fish Pokémon. Famous for being very unreliable. It can be found swimming in seas, lakes, rivers, and shallow puddles.

items.name: Gyarados
items.description: The Atrocious Pokémon. Brutally vicious and enormously destructive. Known for totally destroying cities in ancient times.

items.name: Lapras
items.description: The Transport Pokémon. A gentle soul that can understand human speech. It can ferry people across the sea on its back.

items.name: Ditto
items.description: The Transform Pokémon. When it spots an enemy, its body transfigures into an almost-perfect copy of its opponent.

items.name: Eevee

conditions.value: but the conditions are not well understood
after using two different evolution stones simultaneously
while under ground or in a cave
but the conditions are not well understood
and the only damage-dealing move it knows is Tackle

items.description: The Evolution Pokémon. Eevee’s genes are the key to solving the mysteries of Pokémon evolution.

items.name: Vaporeon
items.description: The Bubble Jet Pokémon. Its cell structure is similar to water molecules. It melts into the water and becomes invisible.

items.name: Jolteon
items.description: The Lightning Pokémon. A sensitive Pokémon that easily becomes sad or angry. Every time its mood changes, it charges power.

items.name: Flareon
items.description: The Flame Pokémon. It has a flame chamber inside its body. It inhales, then breathes out fire that is over 3,000 degrees Fahrenheit.

items.name: Porygon
items.description: The Virtual Pokémon. The only Pokémon that people anticipate can fly into space. None has managed the feat yet, however.

items.name: Omanyte
items.description: The Spiral Pokémon. An ancient Pokémon that was recovered from a fossil. It swam by cleverly twisting its 10 tentacles about.

items.name: Omastar
items.description: The Spiral Pokémon. Its sharp beak rings its mouth. Its shell was too big for it to move freely, so it became extinct.

items.name: Kabuto
items.description: The Shellfish Pokémon. A Pokémon that was recovered from a fossil. It used the eyes on its back while hiding on the seafloor.

items.name: Kabutops
items.description: The Shellfish Pokémon. A slim and fast swimmer. It sliced its prey with its sharp sickles and drank the body fluids.

items.name: Aerodactyl
items.description: The Fossil Pokémon. A savage Pokémon that died out in ancient times. It was resurrected using DNA taken from amber.

items.name: Snorlax
items.description: The Sleeping Pokémon. Will eat anything, even if the food happens to be a little moldy. It never gets an upset stomach.

items.name: Articuno
items.description: The Freeze Pokémon. A legendary bird Pokémon. It freezes water that is contained in winter air and makes it snow.

items.name: Zapdos
items.description: The Electric Pokémon. This legendary bird Pokémon is said to appear when the sky turns dark and lightning showers down.

items.name: Moltres
items.description: The Flame Pokémon. A legendary bird Pokémon. As it flaps its flaming wings, even the night sky will turn red.

items.name: Dratini
items.description: The Dragon Pokémon. Long thought to be a myth, this Pokémon’s existence was only recently confirmed by a fisherman who caught one.

items.name: Dragonair
items.description: The Dragon Pokémon. According to a witness, its body was surrounded by a strange aura that gave it a mystical look.

items.name: Dragonite
items.description: The Dragon Pokémon. It is said that this Pokémon lives somewhere in the sea and that it flies. However, these are only rumors.

items.name: Mewtwo
items.description: The Genetic Pokémon. Its DNA is almost the same as Mew’s. However, its size and disposition are vastly different.

items.name: Mew
items.description: The New Species Pokémon. When viewed through a microscope, this Pokémon’s short, fine, delicate hair can be seen.

items.name: Chikorita
items.description: The Leaf Pokémon. In battle, Chikorita waves its leaf around to keep the foe at bay. However, a sweet fragrance also wafts from the leaf, becalming the battling Pokémon and creating a cozy, friendly atmosphere all around.

items.name: Bayleef
items.description: The Leaf Pokémon. Bayleef's neck is ringed by curled-up leaves. Inside each tubular leaf is a small shoot of a tree. The fragrance of this shoot makes people peppy.

items.name: Meganium
items.description: The Herb Pokémon. The fragrance of Meganium's flower soothes and calms emotions. In battle, this Pokémon gives off more of its becalming scent to blunt the foe's fighting spirit.

items.name: Cyndaquil
items.description: The Fire Mouse Pokémon. Cyndaquil protects itself by flaring up the flames on its back. The flames are vigorous if the Pokémon is angry. However, if it is tired, the flames splutter fitfully with incomplete combustion.

items.name: Quilava
items.description: The Volcano Pokémon. Quilava keeps its foes at bay with the intensity of its flames and gusts of superheated air. This Pokémon applies its outstanding nimbleness to dodge attacks even while scorching the foe with flames.

items.name: Typhlosion
items.description: The Volcano Pokémon. Typhlosion obscures itself behind a shimmering heat haze that it creates using its intensely hot flames. This Pokémon creates blazing explosive blasts that burn everything to cinders.

items.name: Totodile
items.description: The Big Jaw Pokémon. Despite the smallness of its body, Totodile's jaws are very powerful. While the Pokémon may think it is just playfully nipping, its bite has enough power to cause serious injury.

items.name: Croconaw
items.description: The Big Jaw Pokémon. Once Croconaw has clamped its jaws on its foe, it will absolutely not let go. Because the tips of its fangs are forked back like barbed fishhooks, they become impossible to remove when they have sunk in.

items.name: Feraligatr
items.description: The Big Jaw Pokémon. Feraligatr intimidates its foes by opening its huge mouth. In battle, it will kick the ground hard with its thick and powerful hind legs to charge at the foe at an incredible speed.

items.name: Sentret
items.description: The Scout Pokémon. When Sentret sleeps, it does so while another stands guard. The sentry wakes the others at the first sign of danger. When this Pokémon becomes separated from its pack, it becomes incapable of sleep due to fear.

items.name: Furret
items.description: The Long Body Pokémon. Furret has a very slim build. When under attack, it can slickly squirm through narrow spaces and get away. In spite of its short limbs, this Pokémon is very nimble and fleet.

items.name: Hoothoot
items.description: The Owl Pokémon. It cries out at the same time every day. A long time ago, people cherished it and considered it a divine messenger sent to tell the time.

items.name: Noctowl
items.description: The Owl Pokémon. When it turns its head entirely upside down, you know it’s troubled by something. If you don’t leave it be, it will peck you.

items.name: Ledyba
items.description: The Five Star Pokémon. These very cowardly Pokémon join together and use Reflect to protect their nest.

items.name: Ledian
items.description: The Five Star Pokémon. It flies through the night sky, sprinkling sparkly dust. According to some, if that dust sticks to you, good things will happen to you.

items.name: Spinarak
items.description: The String Spit Pokémon. Although the poison from its fangs isn’t that strong, it’s potent enough to weaken prey that gets caught in its web.

items.name: Ariados
items.description: The Long Leg Pokémon. Every night, it wanders around in search of prey, whose movements it restrains by spewing threads before it bites into them with its fangs.

items.name: Crobat
items.description: The Bat Pokémon. It feeds on the blood of living people and Pokémon. If it can’t drink any blood for even a short while, it becomes weak and unable to fly.

items.name: Chinchou
items.description: The Angler Pokémon. Its two antennae glow softly to lure in prey, making it a useful Pokémon for night fishing.

items.name: Lanturn
items.description: The Light Pokémon. It lives far down in the depths of the ocean. It blinds its prey with light, using the moment they’re dazzled to swallow them whole.

items.name: Pichu
items.description: The Tiny Mouse Pokémon. It still can’t use electricity well. When it’s surprised or excited, it discharges electricity unintentionally.

items.name: Cleffa
items.description: The Star Shape Pokémon. On nights with many shooting stars, they gather in packs and dance in circles. If you should see them, something good will happen!

items.name: Igglybuff
items.description: The Balloon Pokémon. Left to its own devices, it will constantly practice singing. You should make it take a break so it doesn’t hurt its throat.

items.name: Togepi
items.description: The Spike Ball Pokémon. As its energy, Togepi uses the positive emotions of compassion and pleasure exuded by people and Pokémon. This Pokémon stores up feelings of happiness inside its shell, then shares them with others.

items.name: Togetic
items.description: The Happiness Pokémon. Togetic is said to be a Pokémon that brings good fortune. When the Pokémon spots someone who is pure of heart, it is said to appear and share its happiness with that person.

items.name: Natu
items.description: The Tiny Bird Pokémon. The look in its eyes gives the impression that it’s carefully observing you. If you approach it, Natu will hop away.

items.name: Xatu
items.description: The Mystic Pokémon. It’s said that while this Pokémon has the power to predict the future, it’s not powerful enough to change the future it sees.

items.name: Mareep
items.description: The Wool Pokémon. Rubbing its fleece generates electricity. You’ll want to pet it because it’s cute, but if you use your bare hand, you’ll get a painful shock.

items.name: Flaaffy
items.description: The Wool Pokémon. In the places on its body where fleece doesn’t grow, its skin is rubbery and doesn’t conduct electricity. Those spots are safe to touch.

items.name: Ampharos
items.description: The Light Pokémon. The light from its tail can be seen from space. This is why you can always tell exactly where it is, which is why it usually keeps the light off.

items.name: Bellossom
items.description: The Flower Pokémon. A Bellossom grows flowers more beautifully if it has evolved from a smelly Gloom-the more stinky the better. At night, this Pokémon closes its petals and goes to sleep.

items.name: Marill
items.description: The Aqua Mouse Pokémon. When fishing for food at the edge of a fast-running stream, Marill wraps its tail around the trunk of a tree. This Pokémon's tail is flexible and configured to stretch.

items.name: Azumarill
items.description: The Aqua Rabbit Pokémon. Azumarill's long ears are indispensable sensors. By focusing its hearing, this Pokémon can identify what kinds of prey are around, even in rough and fast-running rivers.

items.name: Sudowoodo
items.description: The Imitation Pokémon. It’s so popular with the elderly that there’s a magazine devoted to this Pokémon. Fans obsess over the particular length and angle of its arms.

items.name: Politoed
items.description: The Frog Pokémon. The longer and more luxurious the curled hair on its head, the greater the number of Poliwag and Poliwhirl that will obey it.

items.name: Hoppip
items.description: The Cottonweed Pokémon. This Pokémon drifts and floats with the wind. If it senses the approach of strong winds, Hoppip links its leaves with other Hoppip to prepare against being blown away.

items.name: Skiploom
items.description: The Cottonweed Pokémon. Skiploom's flower blossoms when the temperature rises above 64 degrees Fahrenheit. How much the flower opens depends on the temperature. For that reason, this Pokémon is sometimes used as a thermometer.

items.name: Jumpluff
items.description: The Cottonweed Pokémon. Jumpluff rides warm southern winds to cross the sea and fly to foreign lands. The Pokémon descends to the ground when it encounters cold air while it is floating.

items.name: Aipom
items.description: The Long Tail Pokémon. It searches for prey from the tops of trees. When it spots its favorite food, Bounsweet, Aipom gets excited and pounces.

items.name: Sunkern
items.description: The Seed Pokémon. Sunkern tries to move as little as it possibly can. It does so because it tries to conserve all the nutrients it has stored in its body for its evolution. It will not eat a thing, subsisting only on morning dew.

items.name: Sunflora
items.description: The Sun Pokémon. Sunflora converts solar energy into nutrition. It moves around actively in the daytime when it is warm. It stops moving as soon as the sun goes down for the night.

items.name: Yanma
items.description: The Clear Wing Pokémon. Yanma is capable of seeing 360 degrees without having to move its eyes. It is a great flier that is adept at making sudden stops and turning midair. This Pokémon uses its flying ability to quickly chase down targeted prey.

items.name: Wooper
items.description: The Water Fish Pokémon. Wooper usually lives in water. However, it occasionally comes out onto land in search of food. On land, it coats its body with a gooey, toxic film.

items.name: Quagsire
items.description: The Water Fish Pokémon. Quagsire hunts for food by leaving its mouth wide open in water and waiting for its prey to blunder in unaware. Because the Pokémon does not move, it does not get very hungry.

items.name: Espeon
items.description: The Sun Pokémon. Espeon is extremely loyal to any Trainer it considers to be worthy. It is said that this Pokémon developed its precognitive powers to protect its Trainer from harm.

items.name: Umbreon
items.description: The Moonlight Pokémon. Umbreon evolved as a result of exposure to the moon's waves. It hides silently in darkness and waits for its foes to make a move. The rings on its body glow when it leaps to attack.

items.name: Murkrow
items.description: The Darkness Pokémon. Murkrow was feared and loathed as the alleged bearer of ill fortune. This Pokémon shows strong interest in anything that sparkles or glitters. It will even try to steal rings from women.

items.name: Slowking
items.description: The Royal Pokémon. Slowking undertakes research every day in an effort to solve the mysteries of the world. However, this Pokémon apparently forgets everything it has learned if the Shellder on its head comes off.

items.name: Misdreavus
items.description: The Screech Pokémon. Misdreavus frightens people with a creepy, sobbing cry. The Pokémon apparently uses its red spheres to absorb the fearful feelings of foes and turn them into nutrition.

items.name: Unown
items.description: The Symbol Pokémon. This Pokémon is shaped like ancient writing. It is a mystery as to which came first, the ancient writings or the various Unown. Research into this topic is ongoing but nothing is known.

items.name: Wobbuffet
items.description: The Patient Pokémon. Wobbuffet does nothing but endure attacks-it won't attack on its own. However, it won't endure an attack on its tail. When that happens, the Pokémon will try to take the foe with it using Destiny Bond.

items.name: Girafarig
items.description: The Long Neck Pokémon. Girafarig's rear head contains a tiny brain that is too small for thinking. However, the rear head doesn't need to sleep, so it can keep watch over its surroundings 24 hours a day.

items.name: Pineco
items.description: The Bagworm Pokémon. Pineco hangs from a tree branch and patiently waits for prey to come along. If the Pokémon is disturbed while eating by someone shaking its tree, it drops down to the ground and explodes with no warning.

items.name: Forretress
items.description: The Bagworm Pokémon. Forretress conceals itself inside its hardened steel shell. The shell is opened when the Pokémon is catching prey, but it does so at such a quick pace that the shell's inside cannot be seen.

items.name: Dunsparce
items.description: The Land Snake Pokémon. Dunsparce has a drill for its tail. It uses this tail to burrow into the ground backward. This Pokémon is known to make its nest in complex shapes deep under the ground.

items.name: Gligar
items.description: The Fly Scorpion Pokémon. Gligar glides through the air without a sound as if it were sliding. This Pokémon hangs on to the face of its foe using its clawed hind legs and the large pincers on its forelegs, then injects the prey with its poison barb.

items.name: Steelix
items.description: The Iron Snake Pokémon. Steelix lives even further underground than Onix. This Pokémon is known to dig toward the earth's core. There are records of this Pokémon reaching a depth of over six-tenths of a mile underground.

items.name: Snubbull
items.description: The Fairy Pokémon. By baring its fangs and making a scary face, Snubbull sends smaller Pokémon scurrying away in terror. However, this Pokémon seems a little sad at making its foes flee.

items.name: Granbull
items.description: The Fairy Pokémon. Granbull has a particularly well-developed lower jaw. The enormous fangs are heavy, causing the Pokémon to tip its head back for balance. Unless it is startled, it will not try to bite indiscriminately.

items.name: Qwilfish
items.description: The Balloon Pokémon. Qwilfish sucks in water, inflating itself. This Pokémon uses the pressure of the water it swallowed to shoot toxic quills all at once from all over its body. It finds swimming somewhat challenging.

items.name: Scizor
items.description: The Pincer Pokémon. Scizor has a body with the hardness of steel. It is not easily fazed by ordinary sorts of attacks. This Pokémon flaps its wings to regulate its body temperature.

items.name: Shuckle
items.description: The Mold Pokémon. Shuckle quietly hides itself under rocks, keeping its body concealed inside its hard shell while eating berries it has stored away. The berries mix with its body fluids to become a juice.

items.name: Heracross
items.description: The Single Horn Pokémon. Heracross charges in a straight line at its foe, slips beneath the foe's grasp, and then scoops up and hurls the opponent with its mighty horn. This Pokémon even has enough power to topple a massive tree.

items.name: Sneasel
items.description: The Sharp Claw Pokémon. Sneasel scales trees by punching its hooked claws into the bark. This Pokémon seeks out unguarded nests and steals eggs for food while the parents are away.

items.name: Teddiursa
items.description: The Little Bear Pokémon. This Pokémon likes to lick its palms that are sweetened by being soaked in honey. Teddiursa concocts its own honey by blending fruits and pollen collected by Beedrill.

items.name: Ursaring
items.description: The Hibernator Pokémon. In the forests inhabited by Ursaring, it is said that there are many streams and towering trees where they gather food. This Pokémon walks through its forest gathering food every day.

items.name: Slugma
items.description: The Lava Pokémon. Molten magma courses throughout Slugma's circulatory system. If this Pokémon is chilled, the magma cools and hardens. Its body turns brittle and chunks fall off, reducing its size.

items.name: Magcargo
items.description: The Lava Pokémon. Magcargo's body temperature is approximately 18,000 degrees Fahrenheit. Water is vaporized on contact. If this Pokémon is caught in the rain, the raindrops instantly turn into steam, cloaking the area in a thick fog.

items.name: Swinub
items.description: The Pig Pokémon. Swinub roots for food by rubbing its snout against the ground. Its favorite food is a mushroom that grows under the cover of dead grass. This Pokémon occasionally roots out hot springs.

items.name: Piloswine
items.description: The Swine Pokémon. Piloswine is covered by a thick coat of long hair that enables it to endure the freezing cold. This Pokémon uses its tusks to dig up food that has been buried under ice.

items.name: Corsola
items.description: The Coral Pokémon. Corsola's branches glitter very beautifully in seven colors when they catch sunlight. If any branch breaks off, this Pokémon grows it back in just one night.

items.name: Remoraid
items.description: The Jet Pokémon. This Pokémon clings to Mantine and shares in its prosperity. When its Mantine is attacked, Remoraid will fight alongside it!

items.name: Octillery
items.description: The Jet Pokémon. The ink it spits when escaping is special. It contains a substance that dulls the sense of smell, so Pokémon with keen noses get lost.

items.name: Delibird
items.description: The Delivery Pokémon. It shares its food with people who are stranded. Because Delibird is omnivorous, sometimes it gives those people bug Pokémon.

items.name: Mantine
items.description: The Kite Pokémon. Many people have taken up surfing because they admire how magnificently Mantine swims.

items.name: Skarmory
items.description: The Armor Bird Pokémon. he wing feathers it sheds can be processed and made into knives whose sharpness is recognized by the finest chefs.

items.name: Houndour
items.description: The Dark Pokémon. It cooperates with others skillfully. When it becomes your partner, it’s very loyal to you as its Trainer and will obey your orders.

items.name: Houndoom
items.description: The Dark Pokémon. They spew flames mixed with poison to finish off their opponents. They divvy up their prey evenly among the members of their pack.

items.name: Kingdra
items.description: The Dragon Pokémon. Kingdra lives at extreme ocean depths that are otherwise uninhabited. It has long been believed that the yawning of this Pokémon creates spiraling ocean currents.

items.name: Phanpy
items.description: The Long Nose Pokémon. For its nest, Phanpy digs a vertical pit in the ground at the edge of a river. It marks the area around its nest with its trunk to let the others know that the area has been claimed.

items.name: Donphan
items.description: The Armor Pokémon. Donphan's favorite attack is curling its body into a ball, then charging at its foe while rolling at high speed. Once it starts rolling, this Pokémon can't stop very easily.

items.name: Porygon2
items.description: The Virtual Pokémon. Porygon2 was created by humans using the power of science. The man-made Pokémon has been endowed with artificial intelligence that enables it to learn new gestures and emotions on its own.

items.name: Stantler
items.description: The Big Horn Pokémon. Stantler's magnificent antlers were traded at high prices as works of art. As a result, this Pokémon was hunted close to extinction by those who were after the priceless antlers.

items.name: Smeargle
items.description: The Painter Pokémon. Smeargle marks the boundaries of its territory using a body fluid that leaks out from the tip of its tail. Over 5,000 different marks left by this Pokémon have been found.

items.name: Tyrogue

items.description: The Scuffle Pokémon. Tyrogue becomes stressed out if it does not get to train every day. When raising this Pokémon, the Trainer must establish and uphold various training methods.

items.name: Hitmontop
items.description: The Handstand Pokémon. Hitmontop spins on its head at high speed, all the while delivering kicks. This technique is a remarkable mix of both offense and defense at the same time. The Pokémon travels faster spinning than it does walking.

items.name: Smoochum
items.description: The Kiss Pokémon. Smoochum actively runs about, but also falls quite often. Whenever the chance arrives, it will look for its reflection to make sure its face hasn't become dirty.

items.name: Elekid
items.description: The Electric Pokémon. Elekid stores electricity in its body. If it touches metal and accidentally discharges all its built-up electricity, this Pokémon begins swinging its arms in circles to recharge itself.

items.name: Magby
items.description: The Live Coal Pokémon. Magby's state of health is determined by observing the fire it breathes. If the Pokémon is spouting yellow flames from its mouth, it is in good health. When it is fatigued, black smoke will be mixed in with the flames.

items.name: Miltank
items.description: The Milk Cow Pokémon. Miltank gives over five gallons of milk on a daily basis. Its sweet milk is enjoyed by children and grown-ups alike. People who can't drink milk turn it into yogurt and eat it instead.

items.name: Blissey
items.description: The Happiness Pokémon. Blissey senses sadness with its fluffy coat of fur. If it does so, this Pokémon will rush over to a sad person, no matter how far away, to share a Lucky Egg that brings a smile to any face.

items.name: Raikou
items.description: The Thunder Pokémon. Raikou embodies the speed of lightning. The roars of this Pokémon send shock waves shuddering through the air and shake the ground as if lightning bolts had come crashing down.

items.name: Entei
items.description: The Volcano Pokémon. Entei embodies the passion of magma. This Pokémon is thought to have been born in the eruption of a volcano. It sends up massive bursts of fire that utterly consume all that they touch.

items.name: Suicune
items.description: The Aurora Pokémon. Suicune embodies the compassion of a pure spring of water. It runs across the land with gracefulness. This Pokémon has the power to purify dirty water.

items.name: Larvitar
items.description: The Rock Skin Pokémon. Larvitar is born deep under the ground. To come up to the surface, this Pokémon must eat its way through the soil above. Until it does so, Larvitar cannot see its parents.

items.name: Pupitar
items.description: The Hard Shell Pokémon. Pupitar creates a gas inside its body that it compresses and forcefully ejects to propel itself like a jet. The body is very durable-it avoids damage even if it hits solid steel.

items.name: Tyranitar
items.description: The Armor Pokémon. Tyranitar is so overwhelmingly powerful, it can bring down a whole mountain to make its nest. This Pokémon wanders about in mountains seeking new opponents to fight.

items.name: Lugia
items.description: The Diving Pokémon. Lugia's wings pack devastating power-a light fluttering of its wings can blow apart regular houses. As a result, this Pokémon chooses to live out of sight deep under the sea.

items.name: Ho-oh
items.description: The Rainbow Pokémon. Ho-Oh's feathers glow in seven colors depending on the angle at which they are struck by light. These feathers are said to bring happiness to the bearers. This Pokémon is said to live at the foot of a rainbow.

items.name: Celebi
items.description: The Time Travel Pokémon. This Pokémon came from the future by crossing over time. It is thought that so long as Celebi appears, a bright and shining future awaits us.

items.name: Treecko
items.description: The Wood Gecko Pokémon. Treecko has small hooks on the bottom of its feet that enable it to scale vertical walls. This Pokémon attacks by slamming foes with its thick tail.

items.name: Grovyle
items.description: The Wood Gecko Pokémon. The leaves growing out of Grovyle's body are convenient for camouflaging it from enemies in the forest. This Pokémon is a master at climbing trees in jungles.

items.name: Sceptile
items.description: The Forest Pokémon. The leaves growing on Sceptile's body are very sharp edged. This Pokémon is very agile-it leaps all over the branches of trees and jumps on its foe from above or behind.

items.name: Torchic
items.description: The Chick Pokémon. Torchic has a place inside its body where it keeps its flame. Give it a hug-it will be glowing with warmth. This Pokémon is covered all over by a fluffy coat of down.

items.name: Combusken
items.description: The Young Fowl Pokémon. Combusken battles with the intensely hot flames it spews from its beak and with outstandingly destructive kicks. This Pokémon's cry is very loud and distracting.

items.name: Blaziken
items.description: The Blaze Pokémon. In battle, Blaziken blows out intense flames from its wrists and attacks foes courageously. The stronger the foe, the more intensely this Pokémon's wrists burn.

items.name: Mudkip
items.description: The Mud Fish Pokémon. The fin on Mudkip's head acts as highly sensitive radar. Using this fin to sense movements of water and air, this Pokémon can determine what is taking place around it without using its eyes.

items.name: Marshtomp
items.description: The Mud Fish Pokémon. The surface of Marshtomp's body is enveloped by a thin, sticky film that enables it to live on land. This Pokémon plays in mud on beaches when the ocean tide is low.

items.name: Swampert
items.description: The Mud Fish Pokémon. Swampert is very strong. It has enough power to easily drag a boulder weighing more than a ton. This Pokémon also has powerful vision that lets it see even in murky water.

items.name: Poochyena
items.description: The Bite Pokémon. At first sight, Poochyena takes a bite at anything that moves. This Pokémon chases after prey until the victim becomes exhausted. However, it may turn tail if the prey strikes back.

items.name: Mightyena
items.description: The Bite Pokémon. Mightyena gives obvious signals when it is preparing to attack. It starts to growl deeply and then flattens its body. This Pokémon will bite savagely with its sharply pointed fangs.

items.name: Zigzagoon
items.description: The Tiny Raccoon Pokémon. Zigzagoon restlessly wanders everywhere at all times. This Pokémon does so because it is very curious. It becomes interested in anything that it happens to see.

items.name: Linoone
items.description: The Rushing Pokémon. Linoone always runs full speed and only in straight lines. If facing an obstacle, it makes a right-angle turn to evade it. This Pokémon is very challenged by gently curving roads.

items.name: Wurmple
items.description: The Worm Pokémon. Using the spikes on its rear end, Wurmple peels the bark off trees and feeds on the sap that oozes out. This Pokémon's feet are tipped with suction pads that allow it to cling to glass without slipping.

items.name: Silcoon
items.description: The Cocoon Pokémon. Silcoon tethers itself to a tree branch using silk to keep from falling. There, this Pokémon hangs quietly while it awaits evolution. It peers out of the silk cocoon through a small hole.

items.name: Beautifly
items.description: The Butterfly Pokémon. Beautifly's favorite food is the sweet pollen of flowers. If you want to see this Pokémon, just leave a potted flower by an open window. Beautifly is sure to come looking for pollen.

items.name: Cascoon
items.description: The Cocoon Pokémon. Cascoon makes its protective cocoon by wrapping its body entirely with a fine silk from its mouth. Once the silk goes around its body, it hardens. This Pokémon prepares for its evolution inside the cocoon.

items.name: Dustox
items.description: The Poison Moth Pokémon. Dustox is instinctively drawn to light. Swarms of this Pokémon are attracted by the bright lights of cities, where they wreak havoc by stripping the leaves off roadside trees for food.

items.name: Lotad
items.description: The Water Weed Pokémon. Lotad live in ponds and lakes, where they float on the surface. It grows weak if its broad leaf dies. On rare occasions, this Pokémon travels on land in search of clean water.

items.name: Lombre
items.description: The Jolly Pokémon. Lombre is nocturnal-it will get active after dusk. It is also a mischief maker. When this Pokémon spots anglers, it tugs on their fishing lines from beneath the surface and enjoys their consternation.

items.name: Ludicolo
items.description: The Carefree Pokémon. Ludicolo begins dancing as soon as it hears cheerful, festive music. This Pokémon is said to appear when it hears the singing of children on hiking outings.

items.name: Seedot
items.description: The Acorn Pokémon. Seedot attaches itself to a tree branch using the top of its head. It sucks moisture from the tree while hanging off the branch. The more water it drinks, the glossier this Pokémon's body becomes.

items.name: Nuzleaf
items.description: The Wily Pokémon. Nuzleaf live in densely overgrown forests. They occasionally venture out of the forest to startle people. This Pokémon dislikes having its long nose pinched.

items.name: Shiftry
items.description: The Wicked Pokémon. Shiftry is a mysterious Pokémon that is said to live atop towering trees dating back over a thousand years. It creates terrific windstorms with the fans it holds.

items.name: Taillow
items.description: The Tiny Swallow Pokémon. Taillow courageously stands its ground against foes, however strong they may be. This gutsy Pokémon will remain defiant even after a loss. On the other hand, it cries loudly if it becomes hungry.

items.name: Swellow
items.description: The Swallow Pokémon. Swellow flies high above our heads, making graceful arcs in the sky. This Pokémon dives at a steep angle as soon as it spots its prey. The hapless prey is tightly grasped by Swellow's clawed feet, preventing escape.

items.name: Wingull
items.description: The Seagull Pokémon. Wingull has the habit of carrying prey and valuables in its beak and hiding them in all sorts of locations. This Pokémon rides the winds and flies as if it were skating across the sky.

items.name: Pelipper
items.description: The Water Bird Pokémon. Pelipper is a flying transporter that carries small Pokémon and eggs inside its massive bill. This Pokémon builds its nest on steep cliffs facing the sea.

items.name: Ralts
items.description: The Feeling Pokémon. Ralts senses the emotions of people using the horns on its head. This Pokémon rarely appears before people. But when it does, it draws closer if it senses that the person has a positive disposition.

items.name: Kirlia
items.description: The Emotion Pokémon. It is said that a Kirlia that is exposed to the positive emotions of its Trainer grows beautiful. This Pokémon controls psychokinetic powers with its highly developed brain.

items.name: Gardevoir
items.description: The Embrace Pokémon. Gardevoir has the ability to read the future. If it senses impending danger to its Trainer, this Pokémon is said to unleash its psychokinetic energy at full power.

items.name: Surskit
items.description: The Pond Skater Pokémon. If Surskit senses danger, it secretes a thick, sugary syrup from the tip of its head. There are some Pokémon that love eating this syrup.

items.name: Masquerain
items.description: The Eyeball Pokémon. Masquerain intimidates enemies with the eyelike patterns on its antennas. This Pokémon flaps its four wings to freely fly in any direction-even sideways and backwards-as if it were a helicopter.

items.name: Shroomish
items.description: The Mushroom Pokémon. If Shroomish senses danger, it shakes its body and scatters spores from the top of its head. This Pokémon's spores are so toxic, they make trees and weeds wilt.

items.name: Breloom
items.description: The Mushroom Pokémon. Breloom closes in on its foe with light and sprightly footwork, then throws punches with its stretchy arms. This Pokémon's fighting technique puts boxers to shame.

items.name: Slakoth
items.description: The Slacker Pokémon. Slakoth's heart beats just once a minute. Whatever happens, it is content to loaf around motionless. It is rare to see this Pokémon in motion.

items.name: Vigoroth
items.description: The Wild Monkey Pokémon. Vigoroth is always itching and agitated to go on a wild rampage. It simply can't tolerate sitting still for even a minute. This Pokémon's stress level rises if it can't be moving constantly.

items.name: Slaking
items.description: The Lazy Pokémon. Slaking spends all day lying down and lolling about. It eats grass growing within its reach. If it eats all the grass it can reach, this Pokémon reluctantly moves to another spot.

items.name: Nincada

items.description: The Trainee Pokémon. Nincada lives underground for many years in complete darkness. This Pokémon absorbs nutrients from the roots of trees. It stays motionless as it waits for evolution.

items.name: Ninjask
items.description: The Ninja Pokémon. Ninjask moves around at such a high speed that it cannot be seen, even while its crying can be clearly heard. For that reason, this Pokémon was long believed to be invisible.

items.name: Shedinja
items.description: The Shed Pokémon. Shedinja's hard body doesn't move-not even a twitch. In fact, its body appears to be merely a hollow shell. It is believed that this Pokémon will steal the spirit of anyone peering into its hollow body from its back.
items.specialAbilityText: A Shedinja has both of its abilities, all the time.

items.name: Whismur
items.description: The Whisper Pokémon. Normally, Whismur's voice is very quiet-it is barely audible even if one is paying close attention. However, if this Pokémon senses danger, it starts crying at an earsplitting volume.

items.name: Loudred
items.description: The Big Voice Pokémon. Loudred's bellowing can completely decimate a wood-frame house. It uses its voice to punish its foes. This Pokémon's round ears serve as loudspeakers.

items.name: Exploud
items.description: The Loud Noise Pokémon. Exploud triggers earthquakes with the tremors it creates by bellowing. If this Pokémon violently inhales from the ports on its body, it's a sign that it is preparing to let loose a huge bellow.

items.name: Makuhita
items.description: The Guts Pokémon. Makuhita is tenacious-it will keep getting up and attacking its foe however many times it is knocked down. Every time it gets back up, this Pokémon stores more energy in its body for evolving.

items.name: Hariyama
items.description: The Arm Thrust Pokémon. Hariyama practices its straight-arm slaps in any number of locations. One hit of this Pokémon's powerful, openhanded, straight-arm punches could snap a telephone pole in two.

items.name: Azurill
items.description: The Polka Dot Pokémon. Azurill spins its tail as if it were a lasso, then hurls it far. The momentum of the throw sends its body flying, too. Using this unique action, one of these Pokémon managed to hurl itself a record 33 feet.

items.name: Nosepass
items.description: The Compass Pokémon. Nosepass's magnetic nose is always pointed to the north. If two of these Pokémon meet, they cannot turn their faces to each other when they are close because their magnetic noses repel one another.

items.name: Skitty
items.description: The Kitten Pokémon. Skitty has the habit of becoming fascinated by moving objects and chasing them around. This Pokémon is known to chase after its own tail and become dizzy.

items.name: Delcatty
items.description: The Prim Pokémon. Delcatty prefers to live an unfettered existence in which it can do as it pleases at its own pace. Because this Pokémon eats and sleeps whenever it decides, its daily routines are completely random.

items.name: Sableye
items.description: The Darkness Pokémon. Sableye digs the ground with sharpened claws to find rocks that it eats. Substances in the eaten rocks crystallize and rise up to the Pokémon's body surface.

items.name: Mawile
items.description: The Deceiver Pokémon. Mawile's huge jaws are actually steel horns that have been transformed. Its docile-looking face serves to lull its foe into letting down its guard. When the foe least expects it, Mawile chomps it with its gaping jaws.

items.name: Aron
items.description: The Iron Armor Pokémon. This Pokémon has a body of steel. To make its body, Aron feeds on iron ore that it digs from mountains. Occasionally, it causes major trouble by eating bridges and rails.

items.name: Lairon
items.description: The Iron Armor Pokémon. Lairon tempers its steel body by drinking highly nutritious mineral springwater until it is bloated. This Pokémon makes its nest close to springs of delicious water.

items.name: Aggron
items.description: The Iron Armor Pokémon. Aggron claims an entire mountain as its own territory. It mercilessly beats up anything that violates its environment. This Pokémon vigilantly patrols its territory at all times.

items.name: Meditite
items.description: The Meditate Pokémon. Meditite heightens its inner energy through meditation. It survives on just one berry a day. Minimal eating is another aspect of this Pokémon's training.

items.name: Medicham
items.description: The Meditate Pokémon. It is said that through meditation, Medicham heightens energy inside its body and sharpens its sixth sense. This Pokémon hides its presence by merging itself with fields and mountains.

items.name: Electrike
items.description: The Lightning Pokémon. Electrike runs faster than the human eye can follow. The friction from running is converted into electricity, which is then stored in this Pokémon's fur.

items.name: Manectric
items.description: The Discharge Pokémon. Manectric is constantly discharging electricity from its mane. The sparks sometimes ignite forest fires. When it enters a battle, this Pokémon creates thunderclouds.

items.name: Plusle
items.description: The Cheering Pokémon. When Plusle is cheering on its partner, it flashes with electric sparks from all over its body. If its partner loses, this Pokémon cries loudly.

items.name: Minun
items.description: The Cheering Pokémon. Minun is more concerned about cheering on its partners than its own safety. It shorts out the electricity in its body to create brilliant showers of sparks to cheer on its teammates.

items.name: Volbeat
items.description: The Firefly Pokémon. Volbeat's tail glows like a lightbulb. With other Volbeat, it uses its tail to draw geometric shapes in the night sky. This Pokémon loves the sweet aroma given off by Illumise.

items.name: Illumise
items.description: The Firefly Pokémon. Illumise leads a flight of illuminated Volbeat to draw signs in the night sky. This Pokémon is said to earn greater respect from its peers by composing more complex designs in the sky.

items.name: Roselia
items.description: The Thorn Pokémon. Roselia shoots sharp thorns as projectiles at any opponent that tries to steal the flowers on its arms. The aroma of this Pokémon brings serenity to living things.

items.name: Gulpin
items.description: The Stomach Pokémon. Most of Gulpin's body is made up of its stomach-its heart and brain are very small in comparison. This Pokémon's stomach contains special enzymes that dissolve anything.

items.name: Swalot
items.description: The Poison Bag Pokémon. Swalot has no teeth, so what it eats, it swallows whole, no matter what. Its cavernous mouth yawns widely. An automobile tire could easily fit inside this Pokémon's mouth.

items.name: Carvanha
items.description: The Savage Pokémon. If anything invades Carvanha's territory, it will swarm and tear at the intruder with its pointed fangs. On its own, however, this Pokémon turns suddenly timid.

items.name: Sharpedo
items.description: The Brutal Pokémon. Sharpedo can swim at speeds of up to 75 mph by jetting seawater out of its backside. This Pokémon's drawback is its inability to swim long distances.

items.name: Wailmer
items.description: The Ball Whale Pokémon. Wailmer's nostrils are located above its eyes. This playful Pokémon loves to startle people by forcefully snorting out seawater it stores inside its body out of its nostrils.

items.name: Wailord
items.description: The Float Whale Pokémon. Wailord is the largest of all identified Pokémon up to now. This giant Pokémon swims languorously in the vast open sea, eating massive amounts of food at once with its enormous mouth.

items.name: Numel
items.description: The Numb Pokémon. Numel is extremely dull witted-it doesn't notice being hit. However, it can't stand hunger for even a second. This Pokémon's body is a seething cauldron of boiling magma.

items.name: Camerupt
items.description: The Eruption Pokémon. Camerupt has a volcano inside its body. Magma of 18,000 degrees Fahrenheit courses through its body. Occasionally, the humps on this Pokémon's back erupt, spewing the superheated magma.

items.name: Torkoal
items.description: The Coal Pokémon. Torkoal generates energy by burning coal. It grows weaker as the fire dies down. When it is preparing for battle, this Pokémon burns more coal.

items.name: Spoink
items.description: The Bounce Pokémon. Spoink keeps a pearl on top of its head. The pearl functions to amplify this Pokémon's psychokinetic powers. It is therefore on a constant search for a bigger pearl.

items.name: Grumpig
items.description: The Manipulate Pokémon. Grumpig uses the black pearls on its body to wield its fantastic powers. When it is doing so, it dances bizarrely. This Pokémon's black pearls are valuable as works of art.

items.name: Spinda
items.description: The Spot Panda Pokémon. All the Spinda that exist in the world are said to have utterly unique spot patterns. The shaky, tottering steps of this Pokémon give it the appearance of dancing.

items.name: Trapinch
items.description: The Ant Pit Pokémon. Trapinch is a patient hunter. It digs an inescapable pit in a desert and waits for its prey to come tumbling down. This Pokémon can go a whole week without access to any water.

items.name: Vibrava
items.description: The Vibration Pokémon. Vibrava's wings have not yet completed the process of growing. Rather than flying long distances, they are more useful for generating ultrasonic waves by vibrating.

items.name: Flygon
items.description: The Mystic Pokémon. Flygon is nicknamed the elemental spirit of the desert.  Because its flapping wings whip up a cloud of sand, this Pokémon is always enveloped in a sandstorm while flying.

items.name: Cacnea
items.description: The Cactus Pokémon. The more arid and harsh the environment, the more pretty and fragrant a flower Cacnea grows. This Pokémon battles by wildly swinging its thorny arms.

items.name: Cacturne
items.description: The Scarecrow Pokémon. During the daytime, Cacturne remains unmoving so that it does not lose any moisture to the harsh desert sun. This Pokémon becomes active at night when the temperature drops.

items.name: Swablu
items.description: The Cotton Bird Pokémon. Swablu has light and fluffy wings that are like cottony clouds. This Pokémon is not frightened of people. It lands on the heads of people and sits there like a cotton-fluff hat.

items.name: Altaria
items.description: The Humming Pokémon. Altaria sings in a gorgeous soprano. Its wings are like cotton clouds. This Pokémon catches updrafts with its buoyant wings and soars way up into the wild blue yonder.

items.name: Zangoose
items.description: The Cat Ferret Pokémon. Memories of battling its archrival Seviper are etched into every cell of Zangoose's body. This Pokémon adroitly dodges attacks with incredible agility.

items.name: Seviper
items.description: The Fang Snake Pokémon. Seviper shares a generations-long feud with Zangoose. The scars on its body are evidence of vicious battles. This Pokémon attacks using its sword-edged tail.

items.name: Lunatone
items.description: The Meteorite Pokémon. Lunatone was discovered at a location where a meteoroid fell. As a result, some people theorize that this Pokémon came from space. However, no one has been able to prove this theory so far.

items.name: Solrock
items.description: The Meteorite Pokémon. Solrock is a new species of Pokémon that is said to have fallen from space. It floats in air and moves silently. In battle, this Pokémon releases intensely bright light.

items.name: Barboach
items.description: The Whiskers Pokémon. Barboach's sensitive whiskers serve as a superb radar system. This Pokémon hides in mud, leaving only its two whiskers exposed while it waits for prey to come along.

items.name: Whiscash
items.description: The Whiskers Pokémon. If Whiscash goes on a wild rampage, it sets off a quake-like tremor with a radius of over three miles. This Pokémon has the ability to predict real earthquakes.

items.name: Corphish
items.description: The Ruffian Pokémon. Corphish catches prey with its sharp claws. It has no likes or dislikes when it comes to food-it will eat anything. This Pokémon has no trouble living in filthy water.

items.name: Crawdaunt
items.description: The Rogue Pokémon. Crawdaunt molts (sheds) its shell regularly. Immediately after molting, its shell is soft and tender. Until the shell hardens, this Pokémon hides in its streambed burrow to avoid attack from its foes.

items.name: Baltoy
items.description: The Clay Doll Pokémon. Baltoy moves while spinning around on its one foot. Primitive wall paintings depicting this Pokémon living among people were discovered in some ancient ruins.

items.name: Claydol
items.description: The Clay Doll Pokémon. Claydol are said to be dolls of mud made by primitive humans and brought to life by exposure to a mysterious ray. This Pokémon moves about while levitating.

items.name: Lileep
items.description: The Sea Lily Pokémon. Lileep is an ancient Pokémon that was regenerated from a fossil. It remains permanently anchored to a rock. From its immobile perch, this Pokémon intently scans for prey with its two eyes.

items.name: Cradily
items.description: The Barnacle Pokémon. Cradily's body serves as an anchor, preventing it from being washed away in rough seas. This Pokémon secretes a strong digestive fluid from its tentacles.

items.name: Anorith
items.description: The Old Shrimp Pokémon. Anorith was regenerated from a prehistoric fossil. This primitive Pokémon once lived in warm seas. It grips its prey firmly between its two large claws.

items.name: Armaldo
items.description: The Plate Pokémon. Armaldo is a Pokémon species that became extinct in prehistoric times. This Pokémon is said to have walked on its hind legs, which would have been more convenient for life on land.

items.name: Feebas
items.description: The Fish Pokémon. Feebas's fins are ragged and tattered from the start of its life. Because of its shoddy appearance, this Pokémon is largely ignored. It is capable of living in both the sea and in rivers.

items.name: Milotic
items.description: The Tender Pokémon. Milotic is said to be the most beautiful of all the Pokémon. It has the power to becalm such emotions as anger and hostility to quell bitter feuding.

items.name: Castform
items.description: The Weather Pokémon. Castform's appearance changes with the weather. This Pokémon gained the ability to use the vast power of nature to protect its tiny body.

items.name: Sunny Castform
items.description: The Weather Pokémon. Castform's appearance changes with the weather. This Pokémon gained the ability to use the vast power of nature to protect its tiny body.

items.name: Rainy Castform
items.description: The Weather Pokémon. Castform's appearance changes with the weather. This Pokémon gained the ability to use the vast power of nature to protect its tiny body.

items.name: Snowy Castform
items.description: The Weather Pokémon. Castform's appearance changes with the weather. This Pokémon gained the ability to use the vast power of nature to protect its tiny body.

items.name: Kecleon
items.description: The Color Swap Pokémon. Kecleon is capable of changing its body colors at will to blend in with its surroundings. There is one exception-this Pokémon can't change the zigzag pattern on its belly.

items.name: Shuppet
items.description: The Puppet Pokémon. Shuppet grows by feeding on dark emotions, such as vengefulness and envy, in the hearts of people. It roams through cities in search of grudges that taint people.

items.name: Banette
items.description: The Marionette Pokémon. Banette generates energy for laying strong curses by sticking pins into its own body. This Pokémon was originally a pitiful plush doll that was thrown away.

items.name: Duskull
items.description: The Requiem Pokémon. Duskull can pass through any wall no matter how thick it may be. Once this Pokémon chooses a target, it will doggedly pursue the intended victim until the break of dawn.

items.name: Dusclops
items.description: The Beckon Pokémon. Dusclops's body is completely hollow-there is nothing at all inside. It is said that its body is like a black hole. This Pokémon will absorb anything into its body, but nothing will ever come back out.

items.name: Tropius
items.description: The Fruit Pokémon. Children of the southern tropics eat as snacks the fruit that grows in bunches around the neck of Tropius. This Pokémon flies by flapping the leaves on its back as if they were wings.

items.name: Chimecho
items.description: The Wind Chime Pokémon. Chimecho makes its cries echo inside its hollow body. When this Pokémon becomes enraged, its cries result in ultrasonic waves that have the power to knock foes flying.

items.name: Absol
items.description: The Disaster Pokémon. Every time Absol appears before people, it is followed by a disaster such as an earthquake or a tidal wave. As a result, it came to be known as the disaster Pokémon.

items.name: Wynaut
items.description: The Bright Pokémon. Wynaut can always be seen with a big, happy smile on its face. Look at its tail to determine if it is angry. When angered, this Pokémon will be slapping the ground with its tail.

items.name: Snorunt
items.description: The Snow Hat Pokémon. Snorunt survives by eating only snow and ice. Old folklore claims that a house visited by this Pokémon is sure to prosper for many generations to come.

items.name: Glalie
items.description: The Face Pokémon. Glalie has a body made of rock, which it hardens with an armor of ice. This Pokémon has the ability to freeze moisture in the atmosphere into any shape it desires.

items.name: Spheal
items.description: The Clap Pokémon. Spheal always travels by rolling around on its ball-like body. When the season for ice floes arrives, this Pokémon can be seen rolling about on ice and crossing the sea.

items.name: Sealeo
items.description: The Ball Roll Pokémon. Sealeo has the habit of always juggling on the tip of its nose anything it sees for the first time. This Pokémon occasionally entertains itself by balancing and rolling a Spheal on its nose.

items.name: Walrein
items.description: The Ice Break Pokémon. Walrein swims all over in frigid seawater while crushing icebergs with its grand, imposing tusks. Its thick layer of blubber makes enemy attacks bounce off harmlessly.

items.name: Clamperl
items.description: The Bivalve Pokémon. Clamperl's sturdy shell is not only good for protection-it is also used for clamping and catching prey. A fully grown Clamperl's shell will be scored with nicks and scratches all over.

items.name: Huntail
items.description: The Deep Sea Pokémon. Huntail's tail is shaped like a fish. It uses the tail to attract prey, then swallows the prey whole with its large, gaping mouth. This Pokémon swims by wiggling its slender body like a snake.

items.name: Gorebyss
items.description: The South Sea Pokémon. Although Gorebyss is the very picture of elegance and beauty while swimming, it is also cruel. When it spots prey, this Pokémon inserts its thin mouth into the prey's body and drains the prey of its body fluids.

items.name: Relicanth
items.description: The Longevity Pokémon. Relicanth is a Pokémon species that existed for a hundred million years without ever changing its form. This ancient Pokémon feeds on microscopic organisms with its toothless mouth.

items.name: Luvdisc
items.description: The Rendezvous Pokémon. Luvdisc live in shallow seas in the tropics. This heart-shaped Pokémon earned its name by swimming after loving couples it spotted in the ocean's waves.

items.name: Bagon
items.description: The Rock Head Pokémon. Bagon has a dream of one day soaring in the sky. In doomed efforts to fly, this Pokémon hurls itself off cliffs. As a result of its dives, its head has grown tough and as hard as tempered steel.

items.name: Shelgon
items.description: The Endurance Pokémon. Covering Shelgon's body are outgrowths much like bones. The shell is very hard and bounces off enemy attacks. When awaiting evolution, this Pokémon hides away in a cavern.

items.name: Salamence
items.description: The Dragon Pokémon. By evolving into Salamence, this Pokémon finally realizes its long-held dream of growing wings. To express its joy, it flies and wheels all over the sky while spouting flames from its mouth.

items.name: Beldum
items.description: The Iron Ball Pokémon. Instead of blood, a powerful magnetic force courses throughout Beldum's body. This Pokémon communicates with others by sending controlled pulses of magnetism.

items.name: Metang
items.description: The Iron Claw Pokémon. When two Beldum fuse together, Metang is formed. The brains of the Beldum are joined by a magnetic nervous system. This Pokémon turns its arms to the rear for traveling at high speed.

items.name: Metagross
items.description: The Iron Leg Pokémon. Metagross has four brains in total. Combined, the four brains can breeze through difficult calculations faster than a supercomputer. This Pokémon can float in the air by tucking in its four legs.

items.name: Regirock
items.description: The Rock Peak Pokémon. Regirock was sealed away by people long ago. If this Pokémon's body is damaged in battle, it is said to seek out suitable rocks on its own to repair itself.

items.name: Regice
items.description: The Iceberg Pokémon. Regice's body was made during an ice age. The deep-frozen body can't be melted, even by fire. This Pokémon controls frigid air of -328 degrees Fahrenheit.

items.name: Registeel
items.description: The Iron Pokémon. Registeel has a body that is harder than any kind of metal. Its body is apparently hollow. No one has any idea what this Pokémon eats.

items.name: Latias
items.description: The Eon Pokémon. Latias is highly sensitive to the emotions of people. If it senses any hostility, this Pokémon ruffles the feathers all over its body and cries shrilly to intimidate the foe.

items.name: Latios
items.description: The Eon Pokémon. Latios has the ability to make others see an image of what it has seen or imagines in its head. This Pokémon is intelligent and understands human speech.

items.name: Kyogre
items.description: The Sea Basin Pokémon. Through Primal Reversion and with nature's full power, it will take back its true form. It can summon storms that cause the sea levels to rise.

items.name: Groudon
items.description: The Continent Pokémon. Groudon is said to be the personification of the land itself. Legends tell of its many clashes against Kyogre, as each sought to gain the power of nature.

items.name: Rayquaza
items.description: The Sky High Pokémon. Rayquaza is said to have lived for hundreds of millions of years. Legends remain of how it put to rest the clash between Kyogre and Groudon.

items.name: Jirachi
items.description: The Wish Pokémon. Jirachi will awaken from its sleep of a thousand years if you sing to it in a voice of purity. It is said to make true any wish that people desire.

items.name: Deoxys
items.description: The DNA Pokémon. The DNA of a space virus underwent a sudden mutation upon exposure to a laser beam and resulted in Deoxys. The crystalline organ on this Pokémon's chest appears to be its brain.

items.name: Turtwig
items.description: The Tiny Leaf Pokémon. Made from soil, the shell on its back hardens when it drinks water. It lives along lakes.

items.name: Grotle
items.description: The Grove Pokémon. It lives along water in forests. In the daytime, it leaves the forest to sunbathe its treed shell.

items.name: Torterra
